title: Catholic-National Conservative Party in Bohemia
text: The Catholic-National Conservative Party in Bohemia (), was a <a href="Czechs">Czech</a> <a href="catholic">catholic</a> <a href="political%20party">political party</a> in <a href="Bohemia">Bohemia</a>. Party was founded by former members of the <a href="Party%20of%20Catholic%20People">Party of Catholic People</a> around <a href="Jan%20Dost%C3%A1lek">Jan Dostálek</a>. Party operated in close relationship as a counterpart of the <a href="Catholic-National%20Conservative%20Party%20in%20Moravia">Catholic-National Conservative Party in Moravia</a>. On political congress on 5–6 January 1919, party merged into newly established <a href="Christian%20and%20Democratic%20Union%20%E2%80%93%20Czechoslovak%20People%27s%20Party">Czechoslovak People's Party</a>.
